    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline>Aug<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. 1794<note type="editorial">The identity of the hand is uncertain, and the date is incorrect. Bull responds to the queries raised here in a letter of 3 September 1793 (<ref target="1171.xml">1171</ref>).</note></dateline></opener>
                <p>
                    since I seal’d the letter I found y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> of the lighthouses.<note type="editorial">See <ref target="1169.xml">1169</ref>.</note>
                    but this will serve to ask – is there any modern house at <placeName ref="pl2530">Beaulieu</placeName>, &amp; whose.?</p>
                <p>How does the house of Industry go on. does it continue its manufactures?</p>
                <p>How is <persName ref="pe0383">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Clarke</persName>. my best Complimts to him.</p>
                <p>Is the passage thro’ the <placeName ref="pl2118">needles</placeName> really prohibited to men of war?</p>
            </div>
